00:00:02.760 --> 00:00:04.030
Setup Corporate Exchange Email with the Nokia
Lumia 1520

00:00:04.030 --> 00:00:06.130
Welcome to AT&amp;T "How To" videos.

00:00:06.130 --> 00:00:15.440
Today we will show you how to setup corporate
exchange email with the Nokia Lumia 1520.

00:00:15.440 --> 00:00:21.220
To begin, from the Start screen, tap Email.

00:00:21.220 --> 00:00:27.580
Please Note: To setup an additional account,
from the inbox tap the Menu and then Add email

00:00:27.580 --> 00:00:29.539
account.

00:00:29.539 --> 00:00:34.440
Next, tap Outlook.

00:00:34.440 --> 00:00:51.339
Here enter the entire email account address
and password and then tap Sign in.

00:00:51.339 --> 00:01:01.159
Now enter the domain if requested and then
tap Sign in.

00:01:01.159 --> 00:01:09.430
Please Note: For users with blank domain,
leave this field empty and then tap sign in.

00:01:09.430 --> 00:01:16.190
If a notification screen is displayed tap
Advanced to enter additional account information.

00:01:16.190 --> 00:01:25.550
Please Note: Tap Try again to edit the previous
screen.

00:01:25.550 --> 00:01:32.570
Enter the remaining account information and
then tap Sign in.

00:01:32.570 --> 00:01:37.420
If your corporate email server requires a
device security password to be created, If

00:01:37.420 --> 00:01:40.200
so, tap Set.

00:01:40.200 --> 00:01:49.450
Enter the desired password and re-enter the
password for confirmation and then tap Done.

00:01:49.450 --> 00:01:52.140
First-time users will be taken to their inbox.

00:01:52.140 --> 00:01:56.550
New messages will be downloaded and displayed
here.

00:01:56.550 --> 00:02:01.940
Please Note: Users that have previously configured
an email account on their device will see

00:02:01.940 --> 00:02:06.460
the "Email+accounts" screen.

00:02:06.460 --> 00:02:10.830
Test the setup by sending an email.

00:02:10.830 --> 00:02:21.180
If further assistance is needed, please feel
free to visit our website at www.att.com/biz.

00:02:21.180 --> 00:02:26.749
First time users select your device manufacturer
and model and then click Go.

00:02:26.749 --> 00:02:34.829
You will be able to access "Step by Step Tutorials"
or ask a question in our "AT&amp;T Business Community".

